{
  "message": "test(conformance): more FP-P2D-130 fixtures + pin series to_timedelta output dtype\n\nTwo correctness updates that accumulated alongside the FP-P2D-130\npacket landing:\n\ncrates/fp-conformance/src/lib.rs:\n\n- make_drift_record(...) callers in diff_bool_round_trip_result\n  (three sites): drop the unnecessary &format!(...) and pass the\n  String directly. make_drift_record takes an impl Into<String>\n  so the borrow-of-temporary pattern was pointlessly verbose\n  and clippy's needless_borrows_for_generic_args lint was\n  catching it.\n- Test series_to_timedelta_basic: previously asserted\n  Scalar::Utf8(\\\"01:01:01\\\") for 3661 seconds and\n  Scalar::Utf8(\\\"1 days 01:01:01\\\") for 90061 seconds. These\n  were the output of an earlier string-formatting prototype.\n  The real series_to_timedelta function returns\n  Scalar::Timedelta64 with nanosecond counts so the assertions\n  now compare against 3_661_000_000_000 and\n  90_061_000_000_000. The null-in / NaT-out branch is\n  unchanged.\n\ncrates/fp-conformance/fixtures/packets/fp_p2d_130_*.json\n(5 new):\n\n- fp_p2d_130_dataframe_astype_float_to_int_strict,\n- fp_p2d_130_dataframe_astype_int_to_float_strict,\n- fp_p2d_130_dataframe_clip_both_bounds_strict,\n- fp_p2d_130_dataframe_clip_nulls_hardened,\n- fp_p2d_130_dataframe_round_decimals_strict.\n\nTogether with the earlier fp_p2d_130_dataframe_abs_mixed_sign_\nstrict this brings FP-P2D-130 to the 6 fixtures asserted by\npacket_filter_runs_dataframe_numeric_transform_packet, so the\npacket-filter smoke test goes green.",
